47":4,"948":5,"949":5,"950":5,"951":5,"952":5,"953":5,"954":5,"955":4,"956":4,"957":5,"958":5,"959":5,"960":5,"961":5,"962":5,"963":4,"964":4,"965":4,"966":4,"967":4,"968":4,"969":4,"970":4,"971":4,"972":4,"973":4,"974":4,"975":4,"976":4,"977":4,"978":4,"979":4,"980":4,"981":4,"982":4,"983":4,"984":4,"985":4,"986":4,"987":4,"988":4,"989":4,"990":4,"991":4,"992":4,"993":4,"994":4,"995":4,"996":4,"997":4,"998":4,"999":4,"1000":4,"1001":4,"1002":4,"1003":4,"1004":4,"1005":4,"1006":4,"1007":4,"1008":4,"1009":4,"1010":4,"1011":4,"1012":4,"1013":4}}},"docs":{"docs":{"1":{"id":"/docs","page_id":"/docs","type":"page","content":"Introduction","url":"/docs"},"2":{"id":"/docs-0","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"Welcome to Ambriel's comprehensive fraud prevention and compliance platform documentation"},"3":{"id":"/docs-1","page_id":"/docs","type":"heading","url":"/docs#product-overview","content":"Product Overview"},"4":{"id":"/docs-2","page_id":"/docs","type":"heading","url":"/docs#fraud-prevention","content":"Fraud Prevention"},"5":{"id":"/docs-3","page_id":"/docs","type":"heading","url":"/docs#digital-footprint","content":"Digital Footprint"},"6":{"id":"/docs-4","page_id":"/docs","type":"heading","url":"/docs#device-intelligence","content":"Device Intelligence"},"7":{"id":"/docs-5","page_id":"/docs","type":"heading","url":"/docs#aml-and-compliance","content":"AML and Compliance"},"8":{"id":"/docs-6","page_id":"/docs","type":"heading","url":"/docs#customer-screening--monitoring","content":"Customer Screening & Monitoring"},"9":{"id":"/docs-7","page_id":"/docs","type":"heading","url":"/docs#case-management","content":"Case Management"},"10":{"id":"/docs-8","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"configurations"},"11":{"id":"/docs-9","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs#product-overview","content":"Ambriel offers a comprehensive suite of fraud prevention and compliance solutions tailored for financial services, fintechs, iGaming operators, e-commerce platforms, retailers, and other digital businesses seeking effective risk management tools. Our data-driven technology empowers companies to safeguard their operations from financial crime, make informed decisions, and meet regulatory compliance requirements with greater efficiency. With specialized APIs and services, businesses can integrate Ambriel’s tools individually for targeted needs or as part of a complete risk management strategy. Whether tackling transactional fraud, identifying synthetic identities, or ensuring AML compliance, Ambriel delivers data clarity and actionable insights."},"12":{"id":"/docs-10","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs#fraud-prevention","content":"Ambriel's primary fraud prevention tool is the Fraud API, a versatile and modular API that consolidates digital footprinting, decisioning, and risk scoring capabilities into a single, streamlined response. This unified structure allows businesses to submit data inputs and receive enriched insights, rule evaluations, and risk scores in real-time, enabling effective security strategies."},"13":{"id":"/docs-11","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs#digital-footprint","content":"Ambriel's Digital Footprint capabilities provide critical data for fraud prevention by revealing patterns of online behavior, identifying suspicious activity, and verifying the authenticity of user profiles. The Email API, Phone API, and IP API offer rich insights into linked profiles, data breaches, and the reputation of contact details. These tools help detect fraudulent behaviors early, such as disposable emails, suspicious IP addresses, and potentially compromised phone numbers.\nRead more."},"14":{"id":"/docs-12","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs#device-intelligence","content":"The Device Intelligence suite, available through Ambriel's Device Fingerprinting SDKs and the Fraud API, enables businesses to track device attributes, behavioral biometrics, and patterns of interaction. By collecting data on device configurations, browser settings, and user behaviors, Ambriel helps detect bot activity, device spoofing, and multi-accounting attempts. This proactive layer of protection supports both real-time threat detection and ongoing monitoring.\nRead more."},"15":{"id":"/docs-13","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs#aml-and-compliance","content":"Ambriel offers a suite of Anti-Money Laundering (AML) compliance tools designed to simplify regulatory adherence while enhancing fraud detection capabilities. These tools integrate seamlessly with the Fraud API, providing a holistic approach to financial crime prevention."},"16":{"id":"/docs-14","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs#aml-and-compliance","content":"Ambriel's AML tools are designed to be compatible with the Anti-Money Laundering Directive (AMLD5/6) of the European Union, as well as the recommendations of the Financial Action Task Force (FATF).\nRead more."},"17":{"id":"/docs-15","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs#customer-screening--monitoring","content":"The AML API and Fraud API collaborate to screen customers against global sanction lists, PEP (Politically Exposed Persons) databases, and high-risk profiles. This solution supports continuous monitoring, alerting businesses to any changes in a customer’s compliance status over time."},"18":{"id":"/docs-16","page_id":"/docs","type":"text","url":"/docs#case-management","content":"Ambriel’s Case Management platform provides a centralized hub for managing fraud investigations and regulatory reporting. By unifying fraud and AML data into a shared workspace, businesses can streamline manual processes, reduce investigation times, and improve operational efficiency. The platform includes tools for documenting findings, managing escalations, and ensuring audit readiness."},"19":{"id":"/docs/api","page_id":"/docs/api","type":"page","content":"Api Reference","url":"/docs/api"},"20":{"id":"/docs/api-0","page_id":"/docs/api","type":"text","url":"/docs/api","content":"The Ambriel API is organized around REST. Our API has predictable resource-oriented URLs, accepts form-encoded request bodies, returns JSON-encoded responses, and uses standard HTTP response codes, authentication, and verbs."},"21":{"id":"/docs/api-1","page_id":"/docs/api","type":"heading","url":"/docs/api#fraud-api","content":"Fraud API"},"22":{"id":"/docs/api-2","page_id":"/docs/api","type":"heading","url":"/docs/api#aml-api","content":"AML API"},"23":{"id":"/docs/api-3","page_id":"/docs/api","type":"heading","url":"/docs/api#lookup-api","content":"Lookup API"},"24":{"id":"/docs/ui","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"page","content":"Introduction","url":"/docs/ui"},"25":{"id":"/docs/ui-0","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui","content":"Comprehensive overview of Ambriel's fraud prevention and compliance solutions for digital businesses."},"26":{"id":"/docs/ui-1","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui#product-overview","content":"Product Overview"},"27":{"id":"/docs/ui-2","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui#fraud-prevention","content":"Fraud Prevention"},"28":{"id":"/docs/ui-3","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui#digital-footprint","content":"Digital Footprint"},"29":{"id":"/docs/ui-4","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui#device-intelligence","content":"Device Intelligence"},"30":{"id":"/docs/ui-5","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui#aml-and-compliance","content":"AML and Compliance"},"31":{"id":"/docs/ui-6","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui#risk-assessment-for-businesses-kyb","content":"Risk Assessment for Businesses (KYB)"},"32":{"id":"/docs/ui-7","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui#customer-screening--monitoring","content":"Customer Screening & Monitoring"},"33":{"id":"/docs/ui-8","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui#case-management","content":"Case Management"},"34":{"id":"/docs/ui-9","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#product-overview","content":"Ambriel offers a comprehensive suite of fraud prevention and compliance solutions tailored for financial services, fintechs, iGaming operators, e-commerce platforms, retailers, and other digital businesses seeking effective risk management tools. Our data-driven technology empowers companies to safeguard their operations from financial crime, make informed decisions, and meet regulatory compliance requirements with greater efficiency. With specialized APIs and services, businesses can integrate Ambriel’s tools individually for targeted needs or as part of a complete risk management strategy. Whether tackling transactional fraud, identifying synthetic identities, or ensuring AML compliance, Ambriel delivers data clarity and actionable insights."},"35":{"id":"/docs/ui-10","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#fraud-prevention","content":"Ambriel's primary fraud prevention tool is the Fraud API, a versatile and modular API that consolidates digital footprinting, decisioning, and risk scoring capabilities into a single, streamlined response. This unified structure allows businesses to submit data inputs and receive enriched insights, rule evaluations, and risk scores in real-time, enabling effective security strategies."},"36":{"id":"/docs/ui-11","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#digital-footprint","content":"Ambriel's Digital Footprint capabilities provide critical data for fraud prevention by revealing patterns of online behavior, identifying suspicious activity, and verifying the authenticity of user profiles. The Email API, Phone API, and IP API offer rich insights into linked profiles, data breaches, and the reputation of contact details. These tools help detect fraudulent behaviors early, such as disposable emails, suspicious IP addresses, and potentially compromised phone numbers.\nRead more."},"37":{"id":"/docs/ui-12","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#device-intelligence","content":"The Device Intelligence suite, available through Ambriel's Device Fingerprinting SDKs and the Fraud API, enables businesses to track device attributes, behavioral biometrics, and patterns of interaction. By collecting data on device configurations, browser settings, and user behaviors, Ambriel helps detect bot activity, device spoofing, and multi-accounting attempts. This proactive layer of protection supports both real-time threat detection and ongoing monitoring.\nRead more."},"38":{"id":"/docs/ui-13","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#aml-and-compliance","content":"Ambriel offers a suite of Anti-Money Laundering (AML) compliance tools designed to simplify regulatory adherence while enhancing fraud detection capabilities. These tools integrate seamlessly with the Fraud API, providing a holistic approach to financial crime prevention."},"39":{"id":"/docs/ui-14","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#aml-and-compliance","content":"Ambriel's AML tools are designed to be compatible with the Anti-Money Laundering Directive (AMLD5/6) of the European Union, as well as the recommendations of the Financial Action Task Force (FATF).\nRead more."},"40":{"id":"/docs/ui-15","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#risk-assessment-for-businesses-kyb","content":"Ambriel's Know Your Business (KYB) solution enables organizations to assess and verify the legitimacy of business entities they engage with. By analyzing company registration data, ownership structures, and corporate relationships, the KYB API helps identify shell companies, beneficial owners, and potential money laundering risks. This comprehensive risk assessment supports due diligence requirements and ensures compliance with regulatory standards."},"41":{"id":"/docs/ui-16","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#risk-assessment-for-businesses-kyb","content":"Ambriel's KYB tools are designed to be compatible with the Anti-Money Laundering Directive (AMLD5/6) of the European Union, as well as the recommendations of the Financial Action Task Force (FATF).\nRead more."},"42":{"id":"/docs/ui-17","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#customer-screening--monitoring","content":"The AML API and Fraud API collaborate to screen customers against global sanction lists, PEP (Politically Exposed Persons) databases, and high-risk profiles. This solution supports continuous monitoring, alerting businesses to any changes in a customer’s compliance status over time."},"43":{"id":"/docs/ui-18","page_id":"/docs/ui","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui#case-management","content":"Ambriel’s Case Management platform provides a centralized hub for managing fraud investigations and regulatory reporting. By unifying fraud and AML data into a shared workspace, businesses can streamline manual processes, reduce investigation times, and improve operational efficiency. The platform includes tools for documenting findings, managing escalations, and ensuring audit readiness."},"44":{"id":"/docs/ui/test","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"page","content":"Components","url":"/docs/ui/test"},"45":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-0","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/test","content":"Components"},"46":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-1","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/test#grid","content":"Grid"},"47":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-2","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/test#accordion","content":"Accordion"},"48":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-3","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/test#steps","content":"Steps"},"49":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-4","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/test#tabs","content":"Tabs"},"50":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-5","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/test#code-block","content":"Code Block"},"51":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-6","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/test#cards","content":"Cards"},"52":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-7","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/test","content":"you are documentation engineer, use fumadoc, use mdx, use fumadoc components. rewrite this documentation, make it more clear for end user. dont use same sencentes."},"53":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-8","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/test","content":"The growth of the Internet and its usage leaves a trace of simple, easily accessible information about almost every internet user – a trace that we label “digital footprints”"},"54":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-9","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/test","content":"Digital footprints are also left behind when people are registering, accessing or using your digital products. Trustfull is a cloud-based platform that analyses the information content of such digital footprints, to almost instantaneously evaluate the quality and reliability of your online customers."},"55":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-10","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/test","content":"Our platform examines hundreds of digital footprints arising from user's\nPhone Number, Email Address, IP Address, Device, and Browser Data\nInformation about these digital signals can be retrieved separately or combined together to understand the combined score of the compiled Onboarding Solution"},"56":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-11","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/test#accordion","content":"Based on\nRadix UI Accordion, useful for FAQ\nsections."},"57":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-12","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/test#accordion","content":"Code:"},"58":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-13","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/test#steps","content":"Login to dashboard"},"59":{"id":"/docs/ui/test-14","page_id":"/docs/ui/test","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/test#steps","content":"Go to Aml > Entities"},"60":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"page","content":"AML Compliance","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance"},"61":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-0","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","content":"Ambriel's AML compliance solutions are designed to simplify regulatory adherence while enhancing fraud detection capabilities."},"62":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-1","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#what-is-aml-compliance","content":"What is AML Compliance?"},"63":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-2","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#what-does-ambriels-aml-compliance-solution-do","content":"What does Ambriel's AML Compliance solution do?"},"64":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-3","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#screening","content":"Screening"},"65":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-4","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#monitoring","content":"Monitoring"},"66":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-5","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#data-management","content":"Data Management"},"67":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-6","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#how-does-it-work","content":"How does it work?"},"68":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-7","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#what-is-aml-compliance","content":"The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommends that countries implement effective Anti-Money Laundering (AML) and Combating the Financing of Terrorism (CFT) regulations. The European Union's 5th and 6th Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD5/6) also require screening against global sanction lists, PEP (Politically Exposed Persons) databases, and high-risk profiles."},"69":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-8","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#what-does-ambriels-aml-compliance-solution-do","content":"Ambriel's AML compliance solution is designed to help businesses detect and prevent financial crimes. It does this by providing real-time screening, monitoring, and data management capabilities."},"70":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-9","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#screening","content":"The AML API screens customers against global sanction lists, PEP databases, and high-risk profiles. This ensures that businesses are compliant with AML regulations and can detect potential fraud."},"71":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-10","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#monitoring","content":"The AML API also provides continuous monitoring, alerting businesses to any changes in a customer's compliance status over time."},"72":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-11","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#data-management","content":"The AML API provides a secure and reliable way to manage customer data, ensuring that it is up-to-date and accurate. Additionally, all searches and results are stored in a secure and tamper-proof log for 5 years, providing a complete audit trail."},"73":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-12","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#how-does-it-work","content":"The AML API integrates seamlessly with the Fraud API, providing a holistic approach to financial crime prevention. The AML API is designed to be compatible with the Anti-Money Laundering Directive (AMLD5/6) of the European Union, as well as the recommendations of the Financial Action Task Force (FATF)."},"74":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"page","content":"Entities","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities"},"75":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-0","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","content":"Understand the entities in AML context"},"76":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-1","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#what-are-entities-in-aml-context","content":"What are Entities in AML Context?"},"77":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-2","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#types-of-entities","content":"Types of Entities"},"78":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-3","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#politically-exposed-persons-pep","content":"Politically Exposed Persons (PEP)"},"79":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-4","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#sanctions-lists","content":"Sanctions Lists"},"80":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-5","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#crime-lists","content":"Crime Lists"},"81":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-6","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#watch-lists","content":"Watch Lists"},"82":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-7","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#why-are-entities-important-in-aml","content":"Why are Entities Important in AML?"},"83":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-8","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"How Can You Use Ambriel's Entities Feature?"},"84":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-9","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-to-create-an-entity","content":"How to create an Entity?"},"85":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-10","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#entity-fields","content":"Entity Fields"},"86":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-11","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#what-are-entities-in-aml-context","content":"In the context of Anti-Money Laundering (AML), entities refer to individuals, companies, or organizations that are subject to AML regulations. These entities can be either natural persons (e.g. individuals) or legal persons (e.g. companies). Ambriel's AML solution scans over 120 sources and continuously improves to provide the most accurate and up-to-date information."},"87":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-12","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#politically-exposed-persons-pep","content":"PEPs are individuals who hold or have held prominent public offices, such as heads of state, government officials, politicians, or high-ranking military officers. PEPs are considered high-risk due to their potential exposure to corruption and bribery."},"88":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-13","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#sanctions-lists","content":"Sanctions lists are compiled by governments and international organizations to identify individuals, companies, and organizations that are subject to economic sanctions. These sanctions can be imposed due to various reasons, such as supporting terrorism, human rights violations, or nuclear proliferation."},"89":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-14","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#crime-lists","content":"Crime lists are databases of individuals and companies that have been convicted of or are suspected of committing crimes, such as fraud, money laundering, or organized crime."},"90":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-15","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#watch-lists","content":"Watch lists are databases of individuals and companies that are under surveillance by law enforcement or other authorities. These lists are used to identify and monitor potential security threats, such as terrorists, organized crime groups, or individuals with a history of fraudulent activities. Watch lists can be used to flag suspicious transactions, prevent fraud, and protect against potential security threats."},"91":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-16","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#why-are-entities-important-in-aml","content":"Entities play a crucial role in AML as they can be used to conceal illegal activities, such as money laundering and terrorist financing. Therefore, it is essential to identify and monitor entities to prevent illegal activities and ensure compliance with AML regulations."},"92":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-17","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Ambriel's Entities feature allows you to screen entities against PEP, sanctions, and crime lists in real-time. You can use this feature to:"},"93":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-18","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Verify the identity of customers and suppliers"},"94":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-19","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Check for potential AML risks"},"95":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-20","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Monitor transactions and activities"},"96":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-21","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Comply with AML regulations"},"97":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-22","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml