en standard that connects AI models with external tools and data sources. Ambriel's MCP server acts as a bridge, giving your AI agent access to the full Ambriel API surface."},"467":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-7","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents#authentication","content":"Ambriel's MCP server uses OAuth for authentication. When you first connect, your AI agent will open a browser window prompting you to log in with your Ambriel credentials and authorize access. No manual API key management is needed."},"468":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-8","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents#quick-start","content":"All agents connect to Ambriel using the same MCP server URL. No API key is required — OAuth handles authentication automatically."},"469":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-9","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents#quick-start","content":"When you add the MCP server, your AI agent will open a browser to authorize with Ambriel. Accept the prompt, and the connection is established. Your session is persisted for subsequent uses."},"470":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-10","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents#quick-start","content":"Select your agent above for platform-specific setup instructions."},"471":{"id":"/docs/ui/fraud/digital-footprint","page_id":"/docs/ui/fraud/digital-footprint","type":"page","content":"Digital Footprint","url":"/docs/ui/fraud/digital-footprint"},"472":{"id":"/docs/ui/fraud/digital-footprint-0","page_id":"/docs/ui/fraud/digital-footprint","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/fraud/digital-footprint","content":"Discover how Ambriel's digital footprint tracking helps prevent fraud by analyzing user behavior, device identity, location data, and environmental patterns across your digital platforms."},"473":{"id":"/docs/ui/fraud/digital-footprint-1","page_id":"/docs/ui/fraud/digital-footprint","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/fraud/digital-footprint#what-is-digital-footprint","c